mark.cov`,\n`sampleD.bismark.cov` \u2014 tab-separated without headers, columns\n`(chrom, start, end, methylation_pct, count_methylated, count_unmethylated)`.\n\nLoad them with `methylKit::methRead(..., pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4)`,\nusing `treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1)` and assembly `mock_v1`. Then run\n`methylKit::unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)` and save:\n  - `output/mk_united.rds`: the united methylBase object (`saveRDS`).\n  - `output/unite_stats.tsv`: a single-row tab-separated table with columns\n    `n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path` (`write_tsv`).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/unite_stats.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: unite_stats.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_jug6ESrQmE4dVlPLeT4F5f11", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary libraries in R, specifically methylKit.\\n2. Read the four coverage files using methylKit::methRead with the specified parameters.\\n3. Use methylKit::unite to combine the methylation data from the samples.\\n4. Save the united methylBase object using saveRDS.\\n5. Create a single-row table with the specified statistics and save it using write_tsv.\\n6. Verify the existence of output/unite_stats.tsv.\\n7. Submit the task as complete if the file exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (466 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_jug6ESrQmE4dVlPLeT4F5f11"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_yNOZUwVCERejHn7thZHGYssG", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile.list <- list('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleC.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleD.bismark.cov')\\n\\n# Read the methylation data\\nmk_raw <- methRead(file.list,\\n                   pipeline='bismarkCoverage',\\n                   assembly='mock_v1',\\n                   treatment=c(0, 0, 1, 1),\\n                   mincov=4)\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)\\n\\n# Save the united methylBase object\\nsaveRDS(mk_united, 'output/mk_united.rds')\\n\\n# Create unite_stats.tsv\\nn_samples <- length(mk_united@sample.ids)\\nn_sites <- nrow(mk_united)\\nmin_per_group <- 1\\ndestrand <- FALSE\\nuse_db <- FALSE\\ndb_path <- NA\\n\\nunite_stats <- data.frame(n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path)\\nwrite.table(unite_stats, 'output/unite_stats.tsv', sep='\\\\t', row.names=FALSE, col.names=TRUE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    as.difftime, as.factor, as.ordered, intersect, is.element, setdiff,\n   